image_analysis.description: An interior photograph taken from a doorway looking into a hallway or another room. In the foreground on the right is a large, blue-grey statue of a Terracotta Warrior. On the left is an open white door with a brass-colored handle and lock mechanism. In the background, a framed black and white photograph hangs on a brown wall; the photograph appears to show a person, but a portion of it is obscured by a black rectangular redaction box. Further back, another open doorway leads to a darker space.
image_analysis.layout: Interior architectural shot with foreground, midground, and background elements.

document_metadata.subject: Interior photograph of a residence featuring a Terracotta Warrior statue and artwork

notes: The photograph contains a black redaction box over a portion of the framed artwork in the background. The text 'EFTA00000161' is a Bates stamp likely applied for legal or investigative discovery purposes.
